description:
&lt;p&gt;A great opportunity has arisen for a part time Band 7 Team Leader in Infection Prevention and Control due to promotion of the current post holder. This post is one of three team leaders across the Trust wide team of Infection Prevention and Control Nurses.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be an enthusiastic, dynamic infection prevention and control nurse specialist with substantial experience working as a Band 6 or equivalent infection prevention and control nurse. Experienced in a variety of healthcare settings is an advantage including Mental Health, IDD and Community with a forward thinking approach and enthusiasm for working in a swift paced environment with a friendly dynamic team. Team management experience an advantage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Potentially based in one of two team bases Bulwell, Nottingham or Tuxford, the successful candidate will manage a small team and report to the Lead Matron for Infection Prevention and Control.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact Carol Evans, Lead Matron Infection Prevention and Control on carol.evans@nottshc.nhs.uk or 07585404700&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Alternative contact :&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Jude Robinson, Team Leader IPC/ Lead Matron Infection Prevention and Control on 0781 173 7981 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
